  Section 2(a)(4) of the International Religious Freedom Act of 1998 (
  22 U.S.C. 6401(a)(4)
) is amended in the fourth sentence by inserting , including homeschooling, after prohibitions against the pursuit of education, and inserting prohibition of religious methods of meat production, prohibition of circumcision, prohibition of wearing religious garb after or public office.
